# Pandoc

## Installing

On Ubuntu:

`sudo apt-get install pandoc texlive-latex-extra`
 sudo apt-add-repository http://www.ctan.org/tex-archive/macros/latex/contrib/unicode/

Otherwise, see [Installing Pandoc](http://johnmacfarlane.net/pandoc/installing.html)


## Getting started

The `run.sh` script converts any Markdown document to a PDF, using a custom template and custom stylesheets. Try:

`./run.sh README` or `./run.sh README README.pdf`

If you put files in the `./in` folder, running `./run.sh` (without any parameters) will convert each file it contains.

## Basic Pandoc use

Converting a Markdown file to HTML (works with other formats too):

`pandoc -s MARKDOWN_SOURCE -o HTML_OUTPUT`

Converting an HTML file to PDF:

`wkhtmltopdf HTML_SOURCE PDF_OUTPUT`

For more documentation, see the `run.sh` sources and the [Pandoc Userâ€™s Guide](http://johnmacfarlane.net/pandoc/README.html)
